      "intent_description": "R1 is blocking ICMP from 172.16.0.0/24: inbound ACL R1_IN on router1 interface Serial0/1/0 denies ICMP from 172.16.0.0/24, causing pings from 192.168.0.11 to 172.16.0.11 to fail. Desired outcome: permit ICMP from 172.16.0.0/24 so echo replies reach the source and reachability is restored.",
      "needs_fix": true,
      "problem": "Inbound access-list R1_IN on router1 Serial0/1/0 contains a deny ICMP for source 172.16.0.0/24, preventing ICMP echo-replies from 172.16.0.11 and causing 0/25 pings to succeed.",
      "fix_summary": "Replace the deny ICMP entry in access-list R1_IN with a permit for ICMP sourced from 172.16.0.0/24 (sequence 10) and keep the ACL applied inbound on Serial0/1/0.",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "device": "router1",
          "action": "replace_access_list_entry",
          "target": "R1_IN",
          "parameters": [
            "interface=Serial0/1/0",
            "direction=in",
            "sequence=10",
            "replace_from=deny icmp 172.16.0.0 0.0.0.255",
            "replace_to=permit icmp 172.16.0.0 0.0.0.255",
            "description=Allow ICMP from 172.16.0.0/24 for return traffic to restore reachability"
          ]
        }
      ],
